# 9. 聞きたくなかった言葉

Airi: Sigh...
Airi: It's great that I've been getting more work, but I haven't done any shows lately. I haven't even been able to do any fan meet and greets.
Airi: Oh, it's the manager. I need to ask about my schedule.
Manager: Oh, right. Well, you've been doing so well that we'd like to start pushing you more as variety show talent.
Manager: To be honest, you just don't stand out enough as an idol. We've decided to phase you out of that line of work.
Airi: Huh?
Airi: Hold on a minute! You've decided to do what?!
Airi: I fought back, but the agency wanted to go with what they thought would be most popular. They were convinced that was my only option if I wanted to survive in the industry.
Airi: Ultimately, I decided to move to another agency. The new place was happy to tell me what I wanted to hear at first, but it wasn't long before they went back on their word.
Airi: In the end, nobody in the industry thought of me as an idol anymore.
Airi: Even the fans who used to come and watch me...
Shizuku: That's not true. You're a wonderful idol, Airi.
Shizuku: You give people hope, and are the most—
Airi: Just stop, Shizuku. I get it. I'm not blind, you know. I...
Shizuku: But—
Airi: Please, just stop!
Shizuku: !!
Airi: What do you know, Shizuku?! You've got both looks and talent!
Airi: How could you possibly understand someone without your looks, who can't even get others to acknowledge them no matter how hard they try?
Airi: Everyone praises you as an idol and you barely have to do anything!
Airi: Ah...crap.
Shizuku: Airi...
Airi: I-I'm sorry!
Shizuku: *Sniff*...
Airi: Shizuku! Wait!
Shizuku: *Sniff*...
Shizuku: Not Airi, too!
Airi: Found you! You're Shizuku Hinomori, the one who won the Grand Prix at the last audition, right?
Airi: I'm Airi Momoi! I'll be your rival from now on, so don't forget it! And you'd better not let your guard down, or...
Airi: Hey, why do you look like you're about to start crying?
Shizuku: Oh, well...everything is just so overwhelming...
Shizuku: My friends sent in an application for me without me knowing, and I ended up getting called for an audition.
Shizuku: Then I ended up winning the Grand Prix. Now, everyone is expecting so much from me, but...
Shizuku: Everyone here has so much more experience singing and dancing than I do. I don't want to be a burden on the others.
Airi: Huh... When I heard we had a newcomer with a pretty face, I was expecting someone with more of an attitude.
Airi: Pull yourself together! Now that you're an idol, you can't afford to be timid!
Shizuku: But I...
Airi: Remember, an idol is someone who gives hope to their fans.
Shizuku: Hope?
Airi: Exactly. By giving everything we've got to our role, we're able to pass on those feelings of working hard for tomorrow to our fans.
Airi: That's why it's important for idols to have heart. It's not about looks or talent. It's about having a positive spirit. One that gives hope to everyone around them.
Airi: No matter how uncertain or tough things get, we keep looking forward.
Airi: Here's a towel. Now dry those tears, already. A pretty face like yours should have a smile on it.
Airi: We're in this idol thing together now. But don't think I'm gonna let you beat me, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Right. Thank you, Airi.
Shizuku: (It's because of what Airi told me back then that I've been able to come this far.)
Shizuku: (Although...)
Member A: Shizuku got another solo photo shoot for a magazine cover. This is clearly favoritism.
Member B: Yeah, I guess a pretty face is all they care about. We're clearly better at singing and dancing than she is.
Shizuku: (Everyone is different now. Even Airi...)
Shizuku: (I can't do this anymore...)
Minori: One, two, three, four!
Minori: Darn, I just can't get this move right. Huh? When did it get so late?
Minori: Looks like nobody could make it today. None of them have even checked their messages, either.
Minori: Oh, Haruka! You came! I'm so glad!
Haruka: Where are the others?
Minori: Neither Momoi or Hinomori showed up today.
Haruka: I see. That might actually be a good thing.
Haruka: I wanted to talk to you, Minori. I think I'm going to find somewhere else to read starting tomorrow.
Haruka: It's actually pretty difficult to focus when you're dancing nearby.
Minori: What?! Oh, I guess it would be. You did say you were looking for somewhere quiet, after all.
Minori: I should be thanking you for coming this long. You've been watching over me all this time, haven't you?
Haruka: .....
Minori: I've been able to work even harder knowing that you were here with me. Hehe.
Haruka: That's good.
Haruka: Feel free to message me whenever you like. I'd be happy to walk home with you some time.
Minori: Sure!
Haruka: See you later.
Minori: Haruka!
Minori: I'm going to give this audition everything I've got! I'm definitely going to become an idol just like you!
Haruka: !!
Minori: The kind of idol who is able to give everyone around them hope for a better tomorrow!
Haruka: .....
Haruka: Right. Good luck.
Haruka: It's not what you imagine.
Haruka: Being an idol isn't as wonderful as you think...
